page.title: Thirty Years' War

infobox.caption: ''[[les grandes misères de la guerre]]''<br />(''the great miseries of war'') by [[jacques callot]], 1632
infobox.date: 23 may 1618 – 15 may 1648<br />{{resize|''(29 years, 11 months, 3 weeks, and 1 day)''}}
infobox.result:
[[peace of westphalia]]
<small>
* [[protestant]] princes allowed to continue religious practices
* decline of the [[catholic church]] in northern europe (although not exclusively)<ref>[http://www.articlemyriad.com/consequences-effects-thirty-years-war/ the consequences and effects of the thirty years war] "the later divisions that occurred made europe more like it is now with the catholic areas in the south and the lutherans farther north and more importantly, it took the central power from the catholic church."</ref>
*  protestantism eradicated{{notetag|protestantism was effectively wiped out in what is now [[austria]] and the [[czech lands]] by 1648. for comparison of the 1620 and 1648 situation, click: [[:file:the protestant reformation.svg|here]] and [[:file:the counterreformation.svg|here]].}} or damaged{{notetag|protestantism was damaged in [[hungary]], [[slovakia]], eastern [[silesia]], [[slovenia]], [[croatia]] and [[serbia]] by 1648. for comparison of the 1620 and 1648 situation, click: [[:file:the protestant reformation.svg|here]] and [[:file:the counterreformation.svg|here]].}} throughout [[habsburg monarchy|habsburg domains]]
* [[house of habsburg|habsburg]] supremacy curtailed
* recognition of the independence of the [[dutch republic]] by the [[spanish empire]]
* recognition of spanish sovereignty of [[southern netherlands]] and [[duchy of luxembourg|luxembourg]] by the dutch republic
* rise of [[france]] and the [[bourbon dynasty]]
* rise of the [[swedish empire]]
* decline of [[feudalism]] in [[continental europe]]<ref>{{cite book |last=helmolt |first=hans ferdinand |title=the world's history: western europe to 1800 |year=1903 |publisher=w. heinemann |isbn=978-0-217-96566-8 |page = 573 |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=dlvlaaaamaaj&pg=pa431 }}</ref>
* further decentralization of the [[holy roman empire]]
* [[franco-spanish war (1635–59)|franco-spanish war]] until 1659
* devastation and population loss in europe</small>
